===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|συνεργία||joint work, assistance, help}}, from {{m|grc|συνεργός||working together}}, from {{m|grc|σύν||together}} + {{m|grc|ἔργον||work}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈsɪnədʒi/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{enPR|sĭnʹər-jē}}, {{IPA|/ˈsɪnɚdʒi/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|synergies}}

# [[behavior|Behavior]] of a [[system]] that cannot be [[predict]]ed by the behavior of its [[part]]s.
# {{lb|en|medicine}} Combined [[action]]; the combined healthy action of every [[organ]] of a particular system
#: ''the digestive '''synergy'''''
# {{lb|en|pharmacology}} An [[interaction]] between [[drug]]s where the effects are stronger than their mere sum.
# Benefits [[result]]ing from [[combine|combining]] two [[different]] [[group]]s, [[people]], [[object]]s or [[process]]es.

